Description: Use AC_MSG_WARN instead of calling echo via csh for soplex warning.
 Othwerwise, we'd need to add a build dependency on csh just for this message.
 Note that soplex is nonfree and thus not in Debian, so it will not be found.
Author: Doug Torrance <dtorrance@debian.org>
Last-Update: 2022-06-23

--- a/configure.ac
+++ b/configure.ac
@@ -23,7 +23,8 @@
 dnl Make libcddgmp:
 make -C external cdd
 dnl Check for soplex:
-AC_CHECK_LIB(soplex, main, , csh -c 'echo soplex not found: --soplex will not work.')
+AC_CHECK_LIB(soplex, main, ,
+  AC_MSG_WARN([soplex not found: --soplex will not work.]))
 
 dnl Checks for header files.
 AC_HEADER_STDC
